workshop.internal.entities

Interface WorkshopEntity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<WorkshopEntity>, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuthorityPermission, Classifier, ClassifiersGroup, Department, Employee, ExternalAuthority, InternalAuthority, Order, Phone, Position, Task, User, Uuid, WorkshopAudibleEntityAbstract, WorkshopEntityAbstract, WorkshopEntityType

    public interface WorkshopEntity
extends java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<WorkshopEntity>
    Every instance has to be named with a simple noun with a single word without changeable last part of it by plural form, e.g. 'Word', 'Task' etc with 'words', 'tasks'. Also the name doesn't have to include intermediate hyphens. All above are for the sake of constructing simple URI paths '/domainPath/words/', '/domainPath/tasks/' etc. In other cases you will need to correct WorkshopPermissionEvaluator#evaluateServletWebRequest method for proper evaluating getWorkshopEntityName() from a URI path.

    Any implementations are intended to be exposed as the Resource for HATEOAS and also have extended Spring ResourceSupport
